  <!-- ========== BIOMECHANICS ========== -->
  <section id="biomechanics" class="section">
    <h2>Biomechanics</h2>
    <p>Explore optimal hand and finger positioning. Flattened thumb or pinky can cause 
       tension leading to shaky aim. Learn to keep both sides balanced.</p>
    <img src="images/hand-posture.png" alt="Hand Posture Example" class="responsive-img" />
    <ul>
      <li>Relaxed pinky and thumb for smooth left/right motion.</li>
      <li>Elbow ~90°, shoulder loose to avoid transferring tension down to the wrist.</li>
      <li>Find a grip style (palm/claw/fingertip) that supports easy pivot.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== ATTENTION & REINTEGRATION ========== -->
  <section id="attention" class="section">
    <h2>Attention &amp; Reintegration</h2>
    <p>Rather than hyper-focusing on your wrist or the enemy’s position, anchor your awareness in a 
       wide-field visual state. This allows faster “re-binding” after any shock (flash, bump, etc.).</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Wide-Field Vision:</strong> Keep the entire screen in view, using peripheral cues.</li>
      <li><strong>Neural Coherence:</strong> A steady top-down rhythm helps your motor system 
          self-correct smoothly.</li>
      <li><strong>Quick Recovery:</strong> If you tense up, re-center visually and let the posture 
          follow automatically.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== PRACTICE DRILLS ========== -->
  <section id="drills" class="section">
    <h2>Practice Drills</h2>
    <p>Structured routines to build muscle memory without reinforcing bad habits.</p>
    <div class="drills-grid">
      <div class="drill-card">
        <h3>Warmup Routine</h3>
        <p>Spend 5 minutes on posture checks. Gently curl pinky and thumb. 
           Practice wide-field scanning in an aim trainer (e.g. KovaaK’s or Aim Lab).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="drill-card">
        <h3>Multi-Target Flicks</h3>
        <p>Set up a scenario with multiple sporadic targets. Keep your gaze broad; 
           let the crosshair move where your peripheral vision senses a target.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="drill-card">
        <h3>Chaos Recovery</h3>
        <p>Simulate random flashes or obstacles. Immediately reset to wide-field 
           upon recovery and notice how quickly your aim stabilizes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

